item.name: Changelog
item.description:
Coming soon:  
\-test  
\-adding support for fetching list of activity codes  
\-adding support for filtering on open/completed workflows  
\-adding support for inlcuding family and family.member data when fetching contacts.  
\-adding support for completing, creating, and updating workflow tasks  
\-adding support for creating workflows via templates  
\-Adding optional 'include' header to contact notes endpoint.  
\-Breaking change: No longer returning join-table "id" attribute in activity linked_contacts items. Adding/removing contacts is done via the contact_id attribute.  
\-Breaking change: changing workflow linked_contact "name" to "full_name" for consistency with other linked_contact lists.

8/6/20:

- Adding new routes for retrieving birthday and client review reminders
- Breaking changes to opportunities endpoints:
    - Removing opportunity_contacts response nodes and replacing with linked_contacts. Linked_contacts includes additional contact information such as type and name.
    - No longer returning associated records by default. To retrieve associated records, use the "include" header.  
        7/22/20:
- Adding new routes for completing workflow step tasks
- Adding new routes for completing workflow steps  
    7/15/20
- Changing response formats for /lists/database_teams endpoints.
    - On index:
        - database_teams json key changing to teams
    - On show:
        - database_team json key changing to team
    - On All:
        - crm_team_members json key changing to members  
            6/30/20
- Adding "include" header for activities endpoints. If none specified, the default relationships included in the response will be attendees and linked_contacts.  
    6/3/20
- Changed routes for contacts/:id/families to contact/:id/family
- Changed routes for contacts/:id/important_informations to contacts/:id/important_information
- Changed routes for contacts/:id/sams to contacts/:id/sam
- Changed routes for contacts/:id/taxes to contacts/:id/tax
- Changed routes for contacts/:id/personal_profiles to contacts/:id/personal_profile
- Added routes for contacts/:id/identifications
- Added pass through attribute support Seminars(see added examples in Seminar Create POST, Seminar Update PUT)
- Added Count query string parameter to Seminars to include attendee_count & guest_count to Seminars
- Added start_date query string parameter to filter on only seminars occurring after a specified date
- Added more attributes to Contact Methods
    

5/20/20

- Activities: Added pass-through support for activity associations (accounts, seminars, opportunities)
- Activities: Replaced "contacts" and "activity_contacts" JSON nodes with "linked_contacts"
    

4/29/20 - V1 Rollout

response.name: Contacts Search by category ids

header.description: use the include header to attach contact dependent records to each contact in the response.

query.description: search against a first name
search against a last name
search against a status
search against a category
search against an account number
search against a phone, formatting stripped
search against an email address
searches against the fullname in a  'firstname lastname'  format for individual type contacts and company_name for all other types.
searches against the tax identifier
searches against the tag group identifier
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) an email.
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) a phone.
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) an address.
searches against deleted status. inputs are false|true|all
searches against the updated_at field, and only returns contacts that have an updated_at value greater than the updated_since query param
searches against contact types. Valid values are  Individual,Business,Association,Trust,Union

search against a status
search against a category
search against an account number
search against a phone, formatting stripped
searches against the fullname in a  'firstname lastname'  format for individual type contacts and company_name for all other types.
searches against the tax identifier
searches against the tag group identifier
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) an email.
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) a phone.
searches against contacts that either have (true) or do not have (false) an address.
searches against deleted status. inputs are false|true|all

request.description:
At the time of writing, TWAPI only supports creating workflows from templates.

assigned_user_id: The user or team ID that the workflow should be assigned to.

assigned_user_type:

|value|description|
|--|--|
|1|User|
|2|Team|

category_id: for a list of categories, user the /lists/categories resources.

item.description:
**Changing/setting the step due date**

Due dates are determined by the frequency, interval, and interval_placement fields on the step, and are relative to the workflow target date.

**Interval and Frequency**

Interval can be thought of as the amount of time we want to apply, and Frequency is the unit of time.  Frequencies are measured in days (frequency = 1), weeks (frequency = 2), or months (frequency = 3).


**Interval Placement**

Interval placement determins whether our due-date offset is before (interval_placement = 1), after (interval_placement = 2), or on (interval_placement = 3) the workflow target date.

**Putting It All Together**

For example:

9 days before target date = interval:9, frequency:1, interval_placement:1

2 weeks after target date= interval:2, frequency:2, interval_placement:2

1 month before target date = interval:1, frequency:3, interval_placement:1

on the target date = interval:null, frequency:null, interval_placement:3
